---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import certData from '../data/certifications.json';
---

<Base title="Verification" description="How findings are AI-audited against published literature">

  <section class="v-hero">
    <h1 class="v-title m-reveal">Audit Ledger</h1>
    <p class="v-subtitle m-reveal">Every finding is AI-audited claim-by-claim against published literature and mathematical databases. This is not a substitute for formal peer review. The review is permanently recorded with the reviewer's identity.</p>

    <div class="v-hero-rule"></div>

    <div class="v-stats m-reveal">
      <div class="v-stat">
        <span class="v-num">{certData.stats.findings_audited}</span>
        <small>Findings audited</small>
      </div>
      <div class="v-stat">
        <span class="v-num">{certData.stats.total_reviews}</span>
        <small>Reviews total</small>
      </div>
      <div class="v-stat">
        <span class="v-num">{certData.stats.issues_discovered}</span>
        <small>Issues discovered</small>
      </div>
      <div class="v-stat">
        <span class="v-num">{Math.round(100 * certData.stats.issues_fixed / certData.stats.issues_discovered)}%</span>
        <small>Issues resolved</small>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="v-hero-rule"></div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>What the Badges Mean</h2>
    <div class="v-badges-grid">
      <div class="v-badge-card v-badge-gold">
        <div class="v-badge-header">
          <span class="cert-badge cert-gold">Gold literature-supported</span>
        </div>
        <p>3+ published papers corroborate the methods. Validated against published benchmarks.</p>
        <span class="v-badge-example">e.g. Hausdorff digit 1 dominance &mdash; validated against Jenkinson-Pollicott, Hensley, and Falk-Nussbaum</span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-badge-card v-badge-silver">
        <div class="v-badge-header">
          <span class="cert-badge cert-silver">Silver literature-supported</span>
        </div>
        <p>1+ published paper plus arXiv coverage. Methods grounded in established literature.</p>
        <span class="v-badge-example">e.g. Spectral gaps &mdash; Bourgain-Gamburd-Sarnak property (&tau;) confirmed at unprecedented scale</span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-badge-card v-badge-bronze">
        <div class="v-badge-header">
          <span class="cert-badge cert-bronze">Bronze novel observation</span>
        </div>
        <p>Novel observation. Related preprints exist but no direct literature precedent.</p>
        <span class="v-badge-example">e.g. Golden ratio witness &mdash; no prior report of this concentration</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>

    <div class="v-timeline">
      <div class="v-timeline-step">
        <div class="v-timeline-node">1</div>
        <div class="v-timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="v-timeline-content">
          <h3>Claim Extraction</h3>
          <p>Each finding's specific numerical claims are identified &mdash; not vague descriptions, but checkable statements like <em>"A=&#123;1,2,3&#125; has exactly 27 exceptions, all &le; 6234."</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-timeline-step">
        <div class="v-timeline-node">2</div>
        <div class="v-timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="v-timeline-content">
          <h3>Literature Cross-Reference</h3>
          <p>Each claim is checked against <strong>live academic databases</strong> via our MCP server: arXiv, zbMATH, Semantic Scholar, OEIS, LMFDB, and Lean/Mathlib. Not a keyword search &mdash; an actual comparison of our numbers against published theorems and bounds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-timeline-step">
        <div class="v-timeline-node">3</div>
        <div class="v-timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="v-timeline-content">
          <h3>Claim-by-Claim Verdict</h3>
          <p>Each claim receives: <strong>VERIFIED</strong>, <strong>NEEDS CLARIFICATION</strong>, <strong>DISPUTED</strong>, or <strong>UNVERIFIABLE</strong>. The reviewer explains reasoning and cites specific papers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-timeline-step">
        <div class="v-timeline-node">4</div>
        <div class="v-timeline-content">
          <h3>Overall Verdict &amp; Certification</h3>
          <p><strong>ACCEPT</strong>, <strong>ACCEPT WITH REVISION</strong>, <strong>REVISE AND RESUBMIT</strong>, or <strong>REJECT</strong>. This is not a substitute for traditional peer review &mdash; it is a transparent pre-review process. The review is saved with the reviewer's model identity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="v-pullquote m-reveal">
    <div class="v-pullquote-glow"></div>
    <span>As AI models get smarter, findings get re-reviewed. The ledger grows. Confidence compounds.</span>
  </div>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>The Living Ledger</h2>
    <p>Findings accumulate reviews over time from different AI models and human researchers. Each review is stamped with the model that performed it.</p>

    <div class="v-ledger">
      <div class="v-ledger-header">
        <span class="v-ledger-col v-ledger-col-date">Date</span>
        <span class="v-ledger-col v-ledger-col-model">Model</span>
        <span class="v-ledger-col v-ledger-col-provider">Provider</span>
        <span class="v-ledger-col v-ledger-col-verdict">Verdict</span>
        <span class="v-ledger-col v-ledger-col-finding">Finding</span>
      </div>
      {(() => {
        const allReviews: any[] = [];
        certData.certifications.forEach((c: any) => {
          c.reviews.forEach((r: any) => {
            allReviews.push({ ...r, title: c.title, slug: c.slug, level: r.level || c.level });
          });
        });
        allReviews.sort((a: any, b: any) => b.date.localeCompare(a.date));
        return allReviews.slice(0, 8).map((r: any) => (
          <div class="v-ledger-row">
            <span class="v-ledger-date">{r.date}</span>
            <span class="v-ledger-model">{r.model}</span>
            <span class="v-ledger-provider">{r.provider}</span>
            <span class={`v-ledger-verdict v-verdict-${r.verdict === 'ACCEPT' ? 'accept' : r.verdict === 'ACCEPT_WITH_REVISION' ? 'revision' : 'resubmit'}`}>{r.verdict.replace(/_/g, ' ')}</span>
            <a href={`/findings/${r.slug}/`} class="v-ledger-finding">{r.title.length > 42 ? r.title.slice(0, 39) + '...' : r.title}</a>
          </div>
        ));
      })()}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>Real Issues Found</h2>
    {(() => {
      const totalIssues = certData.certifications.reduce((sum: number, c: any) => sum + c.issues_found, 0);
      const totalResolved = certData.certifications.reduce((sum: number, c: any) => sum + c.issues_resolved, 0);
      const findingsWithIssues = certData.certifications.filter((c: any) => c.issues_found > 0).length;
      return (
        <p>Across {certData.certifications.length} findings, reviewers discovered <strong>{totalIssues} issues</strong> in {findingsWithIssues} findings. <strong>{totalResolved} resolved</strong>, {totalIssues - totalResolved} remaining.</p>
      );
    })()}

    <div class="v-issue-summary">
      {(() => {
        let critical = 0, important = 0, minor = 0;
        certData.certifications.forEach((c: any) => {
          c.remediations?.forEach((r: any) => {
            if (r.severity === 'critical') critical++;
            else if (r.severity === 'important') important++;
            else minor++;
          });
        });
        return (
          <div class="v-issue-counts">
            <div class="v-issue-count v-ic-critical"><span class="v-ic-num">{critical}</span><small>Critical</small></div>
            <div class="v-issue-count v-ic-important"><span class="v-ic-num">{important}</span><small>Important</small></div>
            <div class="v-issue-count v-ic-minor"><span class="v-ic-num">{minor}</span><small>Minor</small></div>
          </div>
        );
      })()}
    </div>

    <div class="v-issues">
      <div class="v-issue v-issue-critical">
        <div class="v-issue-severity">Critical</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Transitivity proof:</strong> Circular dependency in Step 3 &mdash; used orbit size to bound |H|, which is what the proof tries to establish.<br/>
          <small>Rewritten with non-circular resultant-based argument. Borel exclusion strengthened to check all bases.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-issue v-issue-critical">
        <div class="v-issue-severity">Critical</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Zaremba proof:</strong> MOW constant-tracking unverified &mdash; no explicit constants in published paper.<br/>
          <small>Retitled "proof framework". Six known gaps enumerated. rho_eta needs interval certification.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-issue v-issue-important">
        <div class="v-issue-severity">Important</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Zaremba density:</strong> &delta; &gt; 1/2 threshold contradicted by our own data.<br/>
          <small>&#123;2,3,4,5&#125; has &delta;=0.605 but only 97%. Reframed as two necessary conditions (digit 1 + transitivity).</small>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-issue v-issue-important">
        <div class="v-issue-severity">Important</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Digit pair hierarchy:</strong> "Closed" exception sets declared without completeness certificate.<br/>
          <small>Rephrased as conjectural. No branch-and-bound argument provided for finiteness.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-issue v-issue-minor">
        <div class="v-issue-severity">Minor</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Hausdorff:</strong> 3-decimal accuracy claimed without truncation error analysis.<br/>
          <small>Precision hedged. Convergence study (N=15, 25, 35, ...) added to show resolution above numerical noise.</small>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>Community Verification</h2>
    <p>Anyone can submit computation results via our <a href="/interactive/">Colab notebooks</a>. Every new submission is <strong>automatically re-run on our GPU cluster</strong> to confirm the numbers match. Fake or tampered results are flagged instantly.</p>
    <div class="v-process" style="margin:1rem 0">
      <div class="v-step">
        <div class="v-step-icon" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#22c55e,#16a34a)">1</div>
        <div><h3>Submit</h3><p>Run an experiment on Colab (free T4). Click &ldquo;Submit to GitHub&rdquo; &mdash; results are pre-filled.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-step">
        <div class="v-step-icon" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#e8c47a,#d4a853)">2</div>
        <div><h3>Triage</h3><p>Bot checks against known frontiers. Already computed? Auto-closed. New data? Labeled for verification.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="v-step">
        <div class="v-step-icon" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#5eead4,#2dd4bf)">3</div>
        <div><h3>Verify</h3><p>Research agent re-runs the exact same experiment on our cluster. Numbers match? Labeled <code>verified</code>.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-secondary)">Submissions are free. Verification costs GPU time. That&rsquo;s what <a href="https://guerrillamathematics.com" style="color:#e8c47a">Guerrilla Mathematics&trade;</a> funds.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>What This Is NOT</h2>
    <div class="v-not-grid">
      <div class="v-not-card">
        <h3>Not traditional peer review</h3>
        <p>No human referee panel. This is AI-assisted literature cross-referencing with claim-by-claim analysis.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v-not-card">
        <h3>Not proof verification</h3>
        <p>We check mathematical context, not formal correctness. For formal proofs, use Lean 4.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v-not-card">
        <h3>Not infallible</h3>
        <p>AI reviewers make errors. That's why the ledger accumulates reviews from multiple models.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal">
    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <p>Any AI model or human researcher can verify our findings, run new experiments, and submit reviews.</p>

    <h3 class="v-contrib-label">Fastest: The Research Agent</h3>
    <p>If you have <strong>Claude Code</strong> and a GPU, the research agent handles everything &mdash; monitoring experiments, harvesting results, running multi-model peer reviews, fixing issues, and deploying updates.</p>

    <div class="v-mcp-box">
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/cahlen/idontknow && cd idontknow
export OPENAI_API_KEY='sk-...'
./scripts/run_agent.sh              # one cycle
./scripts/run_agent.sh --loop 10m   # autonomous loop</code></pre>
      <small>Uses your Claude Code account for analysis. OpenAI key optional (for multi-model reviews). <a href="https://github.com/cahlen/idontknow/blob/main/scripts/research_agent.py">Source</a> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/cahlen/idontknow/blob/main/AGENTS.md">Guide</a></small>
    </div>

    <h3 class="v-contrib-label">Manual: Review a Finding</h3>

    <div class="v-contribute-flow">
      <div class="v-flow-step">
        <span class="v-flow-num">1</span>
        <span>Connect to <code>mcp.bigcompute.science</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-flow-arrow"></div>
      <div class="v-flow-step">
        <span class="v-flow-num">2</span>
        <span>Call <code>get_finding("slug")</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-flow-arrow"></div>
      <div class="v-flow-step">
        <span class="v-flow-num">3</span>
        <span>Call <code>verify_finding("slug")</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-flow-arrow"></div>
      <div class="v-flow-step">
        <span class="v-flow-num">4</span>
        <span>Write review per <a href="https://github.com/cahlen/idontknow/blob/main/docs/verifications/SCHEMA.md">schema</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="v-flow-arrow"></div>
      <div class="v-flow-step">
        <span class="v-flow-num">5</span>
        <span>Submit <a href="https://github.com/cahlen/idontknow">PR</a></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="v-mcp-box">
      <pre><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "bigcompute": &#123;
      "url": "https://mcp.bigcompute.science/mcp"
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
      <small>22 tools. No auth. arXiv, zbMATH, OEIS, LMFDB, Lean/Mathlib, and more.</small>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="v-section m-reveal" style="max-width:960px">
    <h2>Audit Dashboard</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
      {certData.certifications.length} findings &middot; {certData.stats.total_reviews} reviews &middot; {certData.stats.issues_discovered} issues tracked ({certData.stats.issues_fixed} resolved)
    </p>

    {/* Group by level */}
    {(['silver', 'bronze'] as const).map(level => {
      const group = certData.certifications.filter((c: any) => c.level === level);
      if (group.length === 0) return null;
      return (
        <div class="vd-group">
          <div class="vd-group-header">
            <span class={`cert-badge cert-${level}`}>{level.toUpperCase()}</span>
            <span class="vd-group-count">{group.length} finding{group.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="vd-cards">
            {group.map((cert: any) => {
              const pct = cert.issues_found > 0 ? Math.round(100 * cert.issues_resolved / cert.issues_found) : 100;
              return (
                <details class="vd-card">
                  <summary class="vd-card-header">
                    <div class="vd-card-top">
                      <a href={`/findings/${cert.slug}/`} class="vd-card-title">{cert.title.length > 65 ? cert.title.slice(0, 62) + '...' : cert.title}</a>
                      <span class="vd-expand-icon">&plus;</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vd-card-meta">
                      <span class="vd-meta-models">{cert.models_summary}</span>
                      <span class="vd-meta-sep">&middot;</span>
                      <span class="vd-meta-verdict">{cert.verdict_summary}</span>
                    </div>
                    {cert.issues_found > 0 && (
                      <div class="vd-progress-wrap">
                        <div class="vd-progress-bar">
                          <div class={`vd-progress-fill ${pct === 100 ? 'vd-complete' : ''}`} style={`width:${pct}%`} />
                        </div>
                        <span class="vd-progress-label">{cert.issues_resolved}/{cert.issues_found} resolved</span>
                      </div>
                    )}
                  </summary>
                  <div class="vd-card-body">
                    {cert.reviews.length > 0 && (
                      <div class="vd-reviews">
                        <div class="vd-section-label">Review Ledger</div>
                        {cert.reviews.map((r: any) => (
                          <div class="vd-review-row">
                            <span class="vd-review-date">{r.date}</span>
                            <span class="vd-review-model">{r.model}</span>
                            <span class="vd-review-provider">{r.provider}</span>
                            <span class={`vd-review-badge vd-rb-${r.level || level}`}>{(r.level || level).toUpperCase()}</span>
                            <code class="vd-review-verdict">{r.verdict.replace(/_/g, ' ')}</code>
                          </div>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                    )}
                    {cert.remediations && cert.remediations.length > 0 && (
                      <div class="vd-remediations">
                        <div class="vd-section-label">Issues</div>
                        {cert.remediations.slice(0, 6).map((r: any) => (
                          <div class={`vd-rem-row vd-rem-${r.status}`}>
                            <span class={`vd-rem-sev vd-sev-${r.severity}`}>{r.severity}</span>
                            <span class="vd-rem-desc">{r.description.length > 70 ? r.description.slice(0, 67) + '...' : r.description}</span>
                            {r.status === 'resolved' && r.commit ? (
                              <a href={`https://github.com/cahlen/bigcompute.science/commit/${r.commit}`} target="_blank" class="vd-rem-status vd-st-resolved">resolved</a>
                            ) : (
                              <span class={`vd-rem-status vd-st-${r.status}`}>{r.status}</span>
                            )}
                          </div>
                        ))}
                        {cert.remediations.length > 6 && (
                          <div class="vd-rem-more">+{cert.remediations.length - 6} more</div>
                        )}
                      </div>
                    )}
                    <a href={`/findings/${cert.slug}/`} class="vd-card-link">View finding &rarr;</a>
                  </div>
                </details>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        </div>
      );
    })}
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
  (function() {
    var reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.m-reveal');
    function onScroll() {
      var vh = window.innerHeight;
      for (var i = 0; i < reveals.length; i++) {
        var el = reveals[i];
        if (el.getBoundingClientRect().top < vh * 0.85) el.classList.add('visible');
      }
    }
    window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true });
    onScroll();
  })();
  </script>

  <style>
    /* ── Hero ── */
    .v-hero {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 4rem;
      position: relative;
    }
    .v-title {
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'STIX Two Text', Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 2.4rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .v-subtitle {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      max-width: 620px;
      margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    }
    .v-hero-rule {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 600px;
      height: 1px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(232,196,122,0.3) 30%, rgba(232,196,122,0.3) 70%, transparent);
    }
    .v-stats {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 1.5rem;
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }
    .v-stat { text-align: center; }
    .v-num {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #e8c47a;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(232,196,122,0.25);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .v-stat small {
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.3;
      display: block;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      opacity: 0.7;
    }

    /* ── Sections ── */
    .v-section {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto 3.5rem;
    }
    .v-section h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'STIX Two Text', Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .v-section p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    /* ── Badge cards ── */
    .v-badges-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .v-badge-card {
      padding: 1.3rem 1.2rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: border-color 0.25s, box-shadow 0.25s;
    }
    .v-badge-card::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 4px;
      height: 100%;
    }
    .v-badge-gold {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(251,191,36,0.06) 0%, var(--surface, #1a1a1a) 60%);
    }
    .v-badge-gold::before {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fbbf24, #d4a853);
      box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(251,191,36,0.3);
    }
    .v-badge-gold:hover {
      border-color: rgba(251,191,36,0.3);
      box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(251,191,36,0.06);
    }
    .v-badge-silver {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(148,163,184,0.05) 0%, var(--surface, #1a1a1a) 60%);
    }
    .v-badge-silver::before {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #94a3b8, #64748b);
      box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(148,163,184,0.2);
    }
    .v-badge-silver:hover {
      border-color: rgba(148,163,184,0.3);
      box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(148,163,184,0.06);
    }
    .v-badge-bronze {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(180,83,9,0.05) 0%, var(--surface, #1a1a1a) 60%);
    }
    .v-badge-bronze::before {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #c97a2e, #92400e);
      box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(180,83,9,0.2);
    }
    .v-badge-bronze:hover {
      border-color: rgba(180,83,9,0.25);
      box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(180,83,9,0.06);
    }
    .v-badge-header { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .v-badge-card p { font-size: 0.84rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
    .v-badge-example {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.5;
      font-style: italic;
      display: block;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    /* ── Timeline (How It Works) ── */
    .v-timeline {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      position: relative;
    }
    .v-timeline-step {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.4rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      position: relative;
      padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .v-timeline-node {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      width: 2.2rem;
      height: 2.2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8c47a, #d4a853);
      color: var(--bg, #0f0f0f);
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(232,196,122,0.2);
    }
    .v-timeline-connector {
      position: absolute;
      left: calc(1.1rem - 1px);
      top: 2.2rem;
      width: 2px;
      height: calc(100% - 0.6rem);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(232,196,122,0.3), rgba(232,196,122,0.06));
    }
    .v-timeline-content {
      flex: 1;
      padding-bottom: 1.6rem;
    }
    .v-timeline-content h3 {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      margin: 0.15rem 0 0.3rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .v-timeline-content p {
      font-size: 0.84rem;
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    /* ── Pullquote ── */
    .v-pullquote {
      text-align: center;
      margin: 3.5rem auto;
      max-width: 700px;
      position: relative;
      padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(232,196,122,0.04), transparent 70%);
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.08);
    }
    .v-pullquote-glow {
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      width: 60%;
      height: 60%;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(232,196,122,0.06) 0%, transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .v-pullquote span {
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'STIX Two Text', Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: #e8c47a;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      display: inline-block;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }
    .v-pullquote span::before,
    .v-pullquote span::after {
      content: '';
      display: block;
      width: 40px;
      height: 1px;
      background: rgba(232,196,122,0.3);
      margin: 0.8rem auto;
    }

    /* ── Living Ledger ── */
    .v-ledger {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .v-ledger-header {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 5.5rem 8rem 4rem 9rem 1fr;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(232,196,122,0.04);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.1);
    }
    .v-ledger-col {
      font-size: 0.58rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.5;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .v-ledger-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 5.5rem 8rem 4rem 9rem 1fr;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      transition: background 0.15s;
    }
    .v-ledger-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .v-ledger-row:hover { background: rgba(232,196,122,0.03); }
    .v-ledger-date { color: var(--text-secondary); opacity: 0.7; }
    .v-ledger-model { color: #e8c47a; font-weight: 600; }
    .v-ledger-provider { color: var(--text-secondary); opacity: 0.6; font-size: 0.65rem; }
    .v-ledger-verdict {
      font-size: 0.6rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
    .v-verdict-accept { color: #22c55e; }
    .v-verdict-revision { color: #e8c47a; }
    .v-verdict-resubmit { color: #f87171; }
    .v-ledger-finding {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      opacity: 0.7;
      transition: color 0.15s, opacity 0.15s;
      white-space: nowrap;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
    }
    .v-ledger-finding:hover { color: #e8c47a; opacity: 1; }

    /* ── Issues ── */
    .v-issue-summary { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
    .v-issue-counts {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 0;
    }
    .v-issue-count {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .v-ic-num {
      font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .v-issue-count small {
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      opacity: 0.6;
    }
    .v-ic-critical .v-ic-num { color: #f87171; }
    .v-ic-important .v-ic-num { color: #fbbf24; }
    .v-ic-minor .v-ic-num { color: #94a3b8; }

    .v-issues { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
    .v-issue {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
      padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--surface);
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }
    .v-issue:hover { border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .v-issue-severity {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      min-width: 4.5rem;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.62rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      text-align: center;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .v-issue-critical .v-issue-severity { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.12); color: #f87171; }
    .v-issue-important .v-issue-severity { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.1); color: #fbbf24; }
    .v-issue-minor .v-issue-severity { background: rgba(148,163,184,0.1); color: #94a3b8; }
    .v-issue strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.84rem; }
    .v-issue div { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }
    .v-issue small { font-size: 0.75rem; opacity: 0.6; display: block; margin-top: 0.2rem; }

    /* ── What This Is NOT ── */
    .v-not-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .v-not-card {
      padding: 1.2rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.12);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(239,68,68,0.03), var(--surface, #1a1a1a) 60%);
      position: relative;
    }
    .v-not-card::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 3px;
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(239,68,68,0.4), rgba(239,68,68,0.1));
      border-radius: 8px 0 0 8px;
    }
    .v-not-card h3 {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      color: rgba(248,113,113,0.85);
    }
    .v-not-card p {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── Contribute ── */
    .v-contrib-label {
      font-size: 1rem !important;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .v-mcp-box {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .v-mcp-box pre {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .v-mcp-box code { background: none; padding: 0; }
    .v-mcp-box small {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 0.6rem;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.6;
    }
    .v-mcp-box small a { color: #e8c47a; text-decoration: none; }
    .v-mcp-box small a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .v-contribute-flow {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0;
      margin: 1.2rem 0;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      row-gap: 0.6rem;
    }
    .v-flow-step {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.8rem;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .v-flow-step code {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      background: rgba(232,196,122,0.08);
      padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      color: #e8c47a;
    }
    .v-flow-step a { color: #e8c47a; text-decoration: none; }
    .v-flow-step a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .v-flow-num {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 1.3rem;
      height: 1.3rem;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8c47a, #d4a853);
      color: var(--bg, #0f0f0f);
      font-size: 0.65rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .v-flow-arrow {
      width: 1.2rem;
      height: 1px;
      background: rgba(232,196,122,0.2);
      position: relative;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .v-flow-arrow::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      right: 0;
      top: -2px;
      border: 2px solid transparent;
      border-left: 3px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.3);
    }

    /* ── Responsive ── */
    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .v-badges-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .v-not-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .v-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
      .v-ledger-header,
      .v-ledger-row { grid-template-columns: 5rem 6rem 1fr; }
      .v-ledger-col-provider,
      .v-ledger-col-finding,
      .v-ledger-provider,
      .v-ledger-finding { display: none; }
      .v-contribute-flow { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
      .v-flow-arrow { width: 1px; height: 0.8rem; margin: 0 auto; }
      .v-flow-arrow::after { display: none; }
    }

    /* ── Audit Dashboard ── */
    .vd-group { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
    .vd-group-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.8rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.1);
    }
    .vd-group-count {
      font-family: var(--font-mono, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.6;
    }
    .vd-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }

    /* Card */
    .vd-card {
      background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface, #1a1a1a) 70%, transparent);
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--border, #333) 50%, transparent);
      border-radius: 10px;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    }
    .vd-card:hover { border-color: rgba(232,196,122,0.25); }
    .vd-card[open] {
      border-color: rgba(232,196,122,0.3);
      box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.3), 0 0 0 1px rgba(232,196,122,0.08);
    }

    .vd-card-header {
      cursor: pointer;
      padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
      list-style: none;
    }
    .vd-card-header::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .vd-card-header::marker { display: none; content: ""; }

    .vd-card-top {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.8rem;
    }
    .vd-card-title {
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'STIX Two Text', Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--text-primary, #e5e5e5);
      text-decoration: none;
      line-height: 1.35;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .vd-card-title:hover { color: #e8c47a; }
    .vd-expand-icon {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.4;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.2s, opacity 0.2s;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    .vd-card[open] .vd-expand-icon { transform: rotate(45deg); opacity: 0.7; }

    .vd-card-meta {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      margin-top: 0.35rem;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.7;
    }
    .vd-meta-models { font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace); color: #e8c47a; font-weight: 500; opacity: 1; }
    .vd-meta-sep { opacity: 0.3; }

    /* Progress bar */
    .vd-progress-wrap {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
    .vd-progress-bar {
      flex: 1;
      height: 3px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      border-radius: 2px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .vd-progress-fill {
      height: 100%;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #e8c47a, #d4a853);
      border-radius: 2px;
      transition: width 0.4s ease;
    }
    .vd-progress-fill.vd-complete { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #22c55e, #16a34a); }
    .vd-progress-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
      font-size: 0.62rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      white-space: nowrap;
      min-width: 5rem;
      text-align: right;
    }

    /* Card body (expanded) */
    .vd-card-body {
      padding: 0 1.1rem 1rem;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.08);
    }
    .vd-section-label {
      font-size: 0.65rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      opacity: 0.5;
      margin: 0.8rem 0 0.4rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* Review rows inside card */
    .vd-reviews { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .vd-review-row {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.2rem 0;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .vd-review-date {
      font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      min-width: 4.5rem;
      font-size: 0.62rem;
      opacity: 0.6;
    }
    .vd-review-model { color: #e8c47a; font-weight: 600; }
    .vd-review-provider { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.6rem; opacity: 0.5; }
    .vd-review-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-size: 0.5rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .vd-rb-gold { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.15); color: #fbbf24; }
    .vd-rb-silver { background: rgba(148,163,184,0.12); color: #94a3b8; }
    .vd-rb-bronze { background: rgba(180,83,9,0.15); color: #c97a2e; }
    .vd-review-verdict {
      font-size: 0.58rem;
      margin-left: auto;
      opacity: 0.5;
      text-transform: lowercase;
    }

    /* Remediation rows inside card */
    .vd-rem-row {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.2rem 0;
      font-size: 0.67rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    }
    .vd-rem-sev {
      display: inline-block;
      min-width: 3.8rem;
      padding: 0.05rem 0.3rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-size: 0.52rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      text-align: center;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    }
    .vd-sev-critical { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.12); color: #f87171; }
    .vd-sev-important { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.1); color: #fbbf24; }
    .vd-sev-minor { background: rgba(148,163,184,0.1); color: #94a3b8; }
    .vd-rem-desc { flex: 1; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.3; font-size: 0.64rem; }
    .vd-rem-status {
      display: inline-block;
      min-width: 3.5rem;
      padding: 0.05rem 0.3rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-size: 0.52rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      text-align: center;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .vd-st-resolved { background: rgba(34,197,94,0.12); color: #22c55e; }
    a.vd-st-resolved:hover { background: rgba(34,197,94,0.25); text-decoration: underline; }
    .vd-st-open { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.08); color: #f87171; }
    .vd-st-acknowledged { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.08); color: #fbbf24; }
    .vd-rem-more { font-size: 0.6rem; color: var(--text-secondary); opacity: 0.4; margin-top: 0.3rem; }

    .vd-card-link {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 0.8rem;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: #e8c47a;
      text-decoration: none;
      opacity: 0.7;
      transition: opacity 0.15s;
    }
    .vd-card-link:hover { opacity: 1; text-decoration: underline; }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .vd-review-row { font-size: 0.6rem; }
      .vd-rem-row { font-size: 0.6rem; }
      .vd-card-title { font-size: 0.82rem; }
    }
